Pre-Interview Assignment: University & Course Data Scraping
Objective
Scrape universities and their courses from the web and submit the data in a structured Excel file.
The goal of this assignment is to evaluate your ability to:
Collect real-world data using Python
Clean and structure raw data
Organize datasets professionally
Maintain relational data integrity


Task Details
1. University Selection
Choose any 5–10 universities from any country
 (or from a provided list, if shared).


2. University Data Collection
For each university, collect the following details:
University Name
Country
City
Official Website
3. Course Data Collection
For each selected university, collect at least 5 courses with the following details:
Course Name
Level (Bachelor’s / Master’s / PhD / Diploma, etc.)
Field / Discipline
Duration (if available)
Fees (if available)
Eligibility Criteria (if available)
4. Technical Requirements
Use Python for scraping
Ensure scraping is dynamic and automated (no copy-paste)
Organize and clean the data properly
Handle missing values appropriately
Excel Submission Format (Demo Structure)
Submit one Excel file with two sheets:

Sheet 1: Universities
university_id
university_name
country
city
website

Instructions:
university_id must be unique.
No duplicate entries.
Website links should be official URLs only.


Sheet 2: Courses
course_id
university_id
course_name
level
discipline
duration
fees
eligibility

Important:
university_id must correctly link each course to its university.
course_id must be unique.
Ensure relational integrity between both sheets.


Submission Instructions
Submit 1 Excel file containing:


Sheet 1: Universities
Sheet 2: Courses


Must Include your Python script via:


ZIP file, or


GitHub repository link
Ensure:


Data is clean and readable
No duplicate records
IDs are properly linked
Evaluation Criteria
Your submission will be evaluated based on:
Correctness and completeness of data
Data cleanliness and structured formatting
Proper linking between universities and courses
Scraping quality (automation, not manual copy-paste)
Excel organization and professional presentation


